h1 Frequently Asked Questions

h5 Terminology

p <b>Collections</b>
p What is a collection? A collection is a set of works that have been collected together to form a unit.  Each work must belong to a collection, each page to a work.
p Who can see a collection?  By default a collection is visible to anyone accessing FromThePage from the internet.  This can be changed by the owner of a collection.  
p Can a collection be translated? Yes, a collection or work can be translated.  See the "Managing Collections" section below for instructions.

p <b>Works</b>
p What is a work? A work is an individual item (book, article, journal, letter, etc.) that is uploaded into a collection. A work belongs to a single collection.

p <b>Pages</b>
p What is a page? A page is the smallest unit within a work (such as pages in a book, article, journal, etc.)  It is a single image from a work, generally a single page within a book or a letter, although occasionally a scan can span multiple pages in one image.

p Project
p What is a project? A project is at least one uploaded or imported work within a collection.

p Document Sets
p What are document sets? Document sets are subsets of works in a collection, which can be used to focus an editing project or to create a public exhibition about a particular focus of the documents.  
p How do I create a document set?  You can create document sets when you are the owner of a collection, by going into the Settings tab and clicking on the "Create Document Sets" button on the right side of the page.

