p Categories
p What are categories? Categories are classes of entities that are related to one another.  Categories allow you to visualize relationships between entities (subjects) within a collection.  For example, you can visualize the frequency of an entity's occurence in a collection and compare that with the frequencies of other entities occurrences within the collection.
p Where do categories apply?  Categories and subjects only search and link within one collection.
p How do I create or delete a category? When you are in the Subjects tab of a collection, you can add a category by clicking on the Actions button on the right side of the screen.  Then select a Root/Child category.  You can also delete a category in this view.
