h5 User Roles
p Owners
p What is an owner?  An owner owns a collection or work, with all the associated pages and sets.
p What privileges does an owner have?  An owner has full control over a collection, works and pages associated with them. Owners also have control over the privileges assigned to a work or page.
p Can a collection have multiple owners?  Yes, there can be multiple owners of a collection.
p Can the owner who uploaded the collection be deleted?  No, the original owner (who uploaded the collection) cannot be deleted.

p Editors
p What is an editor? The editor and transcriber roles are currently the same.

p Transcribers
p What is a transcriber? Transcribers transcribe a page in a work/collection.
p Can transcribers edit page titles?  Transcribers can edit page titles if the work owner has given them permission in the work settings tab.
p Who can transcribe a work? Anyone with a FromThePage account can transcribe any work, unless editors have been restricted by the owner of the work.

h5 Transcription Information
p What are transcription conventions? Transcription conventions are the formatting and standards used when a page is transcribed.  Specific conventions for a collection/work can be set by the owner.  The specific conventions for a work are found toward the bottom of a page being transcribed.
